Description:
Semi-Rural Block - Only 500m From Town!
Set back from the road and sited on approximately one and a quarter glorious acres, this fantastic property is like having your very own private resort complete with pool, leafy treed gardens and recreation areas. Three living zones give options for all the family. A rumpus room at the rear of the home allows children to raise a ruckus and not disturb the entire household. The meals area is immense, easily able to accommodate another sofa or two. Open to this area and appointed with top of the range appliances, the kitchen is simply superb. Quality cabinetry, pot drawers, wine rack, walk-in pantry and polished granite benches combine to form a beautiful and highly functional catering zone.
Accommodation includes four bedrooms, main with en suite and walk-in robe. A home office off the entry with an entire wall devoted to built-in shelves has ample space or could be used as a fifth bedroom. Thoughtfully designed to ease the tension of morning peak hour, the shower and bath are in a separate room to the vanity. Heating and cooling are ducted throughout, and a gas wall heater has also been installed in a central position. Double glazed windows are an added benefit!
Salt-chlorinated, the in-ground swimming pool and spa are a dream come true to keep kids happy at home during the summer months. Solar heating extends seasonal use, and the adjoining undercover outdoor living zone is perfect for pool parties.
In the enormous backyard, fencing surrounds a basketball practice area and chicken coop, along with many fruit trees and raised garden beds ideal for growing vegies. Measuring about 147 metres, a magnificent shed contains concrete floor and power, roller doors, benches and shelving. A 53 metre garden shed also has concrete floor and though on town water, two tanks supply 44,000 litre rainwater capacity.
In very close proximity to schools, shopping and much more, this wonderful family property will be hard to beat.
Insights: 71 Princess Street, Drysdale VIC 3222 was last sold in 2017 and 2 other 5 bedroom house in Drysdale have recently been sold.

Description:
Immaculate, Spacious Home in Park Setting
Established trees on this expansive 1343m2 block create a park-like setting for this substantial home close to the Drysdale town centre. Perfectly located for the growing family and within walking distance to kinder, primary and secondary schools. The vendor's ongoing attention to detail and regular maintenance in and around the home place it in tip top condition.
On entry you will be delighted by the light and bright interior which flows to the formal dining area and lounge room at the forefront of the home. Space to escape from the family and put your feet up and relax. The kitchen is both modern and functional consisting of walk-in pantry, quality cabinetry in neutral tones, modern appliances and ample cupboard space.
There are five generous sized bedrooms, two of which have a sitting or study area. The main bedroom with ensuite has ample built in storage and ceiling fan. Light and bright family bathroom with separate toilet. Family time can be spent in the massive rumpus room at the rear of the home with access to the outdoor undercover barbeque and entertaining area with an additional powder room servicing the fourth and fifth queen-sized bedrooms. A dedicated study and substantial storage throughout complete this spacious family home.
Outside there are nooks and crannies a plenty for play in the garden and lawned areas. Established fruit trees sit at the rear of the block beside a double garage or workshop.
Extras include reverse cycle air conditioners,
walk-in pantry, ducted vacuum system, abundant storage areas, gas heating, abundant parking and excellent fencing.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
A convenient lifestyle property
Set on the tranquil outskirts of Drysdale, Buccleugh Street delivers a true rural experience.
This solid and brick home, on 3026 sqm (approx) has a desirable lifestyle presence that will appeal to those seeking space and tranquility in a bayside location, close to all family amenities, wineries and divine local produce. The circular driveway is welcoming and amplifies the sense of space at the facade. The big northern aspect to the rear provides plenty of space for a swimming pool or other lifestyle assets. Complimentary gardens create relaxing outlooks from indoors, and nestle the private outdoor entertaining zone.
The home boasts generous light-filled rooms, multiple living areas and timeless country charm that is easily personalised. The inclusive open plan kitchen/living/dining space features a wall of glass to the north that frames alfresco entertaining and the peaceful grounds beyond. The living zone offers a new split system AC, and access to the patio with Wisteria pergola. The dining zone is proportioned for a family. The kitchen is social and enjoyable, with wide garden views, near-new electric oven and dishwasher, and gas cooktop.
The master bedroom with walk-in robe, ensuite and garden access sits peacefully at the end of the zone-able bedroom wing. Two further bedrooms with robes share a fresh family bathroom and separate toilet. The dedicated office at the facade is ideal for a home business. The double garage features double roller doors to the front and rear providing easy access to the backyard. Gates allow high-clearance access to the backyard. There is also 5x4m (approx) shed with concrete floor and power, plus small shed and chicken coop.
Exceptionally private backyard is protected from the prevailing south-westerly weather. The corner position allows potential access for a tradesman, with space for a workshop, without visual impact to the home.
- 3026sqm on the outskirts of Drysdale
- Spacious 3-bedroom brick home with large light-filled rooms
- Northern aspect to living, outdoor entertaining and the backyard
- Master with en suite, WIR and garden access
- Office, DLUG and a 5x4m (approx) shed
- Space to extend or put in a pool (STCA)

Description:
Custom Designed Family Haven
Just 3 years old, this custom home is 'big' on all the little details that make the difference between a house and a magnificent family residence. Constructed by Armistead Homes, this chic home brings to life an original floorplan, tailored specifically to family-life. Centrally positioned, the home is walking distance to the shops and a range of well-reputed schools, and only 10min to the beach at Portarlington or Ocean Grove.
Bespoke interiors reflect a coastal aesthetic with an abundance of natural light throughout. The smart floor plan provides a balance of space for entertaining and me time with two living zones, kitchen and paved alfresco to the ground floor, and four bedrooms placed above. Outstanding for family-sized catering, the kitchen has a large walk-in pantry, 900mm stainless steel upright cooker, Bosch dishwasher and spacious wrap-around island bench. Ground floor extras include a sumptuous window seat (with built-in storage) to the lounge, a study nook that allows you to keep an eye on dinner while you work, and a convenient powder room.
Upstairs, the elegant master bed doesn't skip a beat with bedside pendant lights, premium en suite, fully fitted walk-in robe, window seat and SS-AC. The 3 minor bedrooms aren't short on space, built-in storage or natural light, and open to a cosy retreat, with access to the attractive bathroom and separate toilet.
Just some of the highlights of this impressive home include 40mm Caesarstone benchtops throughout, under mount sinks to kitchen and bathrooms, oversized showers with tiled bases, double glazing, Nobo panel heaters (to lounge and bedrooms), Inverter AC and gas log fire (to living), Tasmanian Oak floorboards, a low maintenance garden with a small orchard, and a double lock-up garage.
Far beyond standard, this 'as new' custom home is brimming with quality inclusions that elevate daily living to a zone of pure comfort. Savour the details as you enjoy an inspection.

Description:
Significant Family Home
This significant family residence boast a stunning modern layout and is located close to the Drysdale shopping hub, schools, sporting clubs and other amenities.
The floorplan features significant living zones and four generous bedrooms (master with ensuite and walk in robe). There's more than enough space for the kids to play in the large rumpus room, and the bright open plan kitchen, dining and living area make it perfect for entertaining. A separate study or fifth bedroom offers versatility.
Double doors open out to the spacious undercover alfresco decking area which partially wraps around the home, looking out to the established and neatly kept garden. The rear features an array of leafy trees and backs on to a reserve creating a wonderful sense of tranquillity and space. The sizeable water tank and aviary are a nice touch.
Features include ducted heating and cooling, polished floor boards, spa bath, stainless steel appliances and elevated ceiling heights.
A massive remote double lock up garage with internal access is ideal for car storage.
This home has it all, it's just waiting for you to move in!

Description:
‘Rural’ Serenity In Town!
Experience the best of both worlds! From a big block size, a gorgeous rural-style view, to a central location in popular Drysdale, this charming home is the answer for house-hunters looking for more space close to town!
Set on over 700 sqm (approx.), the feeling of space is enhanced by the calm, semi-rural style outlook to the rear, and peaceful walking trails beyond the back gate! Close to the Bellarine Rail Trail, Lake Lorne Reserve, Drysdale Recreation Reserve, major bus routes, shopping precinct, and schools, this location puts the ‘c’ in ‘central’!
Inside, the comfortable floorplan blends indoor and outdoor living, with the lounge and balcony overlooking the green, tree-dotted expanse of neighbouring properties. The open-plan kitchen, living and dining area sits at the heart of the home. The kitchen has a practical walk-in pantry and leads into the compact home office. The master bedroom has an en suite and built-in storage, while two kids bedrooms (with built-in robes) access the bathroom and separate toilet. Other features include SS-AC and polished floorboards.
Extensive parking and storage is a huge plus- with two carports, a secure lock-up garage and large workshop offering a bounty of space for vehicles, boat and trailer, and your hobbies and projects.
With space aplenty, and a view that most would kill for this close to town, this family home is something very special! Inspect to appreciate.
